2ï¸âƒ£ find
âœ… Purpose
Find files by name, size, time, type.

Disk is full.
Now find large files:
find / -type f -size +1G
Explanation:
/ â†’ search entire system
-type f â†’ only files
-size +1G â†’ larger than 1GB
You immediately see which file consuming space.

Find Specific File Type
Find all .conf files:
find /etc -name "*.conf"

find /var/log/myapp  -name  *.log
/var/log/myapp/app.log

