3ï¸âƒ£ awk
âœ… Purpose
Text processing & column extraction.
ğŸ”¥ Production Use Case
Log format:
IP - - [date] "GET /index.html" 200
Need only IPs:
awk '{print $1}' access.log

example

 awk '{print $1}' /var/log/myapp/app.log
[200~2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21
2026-02-21

awk -F'-' '{print $1}' /var/log/myapp/app.log
-F'-' â†’ tells awk to split using -
print $1 â†’ prints first field before -
2026
2026
2026
...
If You Want Only One Unique Year
awk -F'-' '{print $1}' /var/log/myapp/app.log | uniq
Or safer:
awk -F'-' '{print $1}' /var/log/myapp/app.log | sort -u

