4ï¸âƒ£ sed
âœ… Purpose
Find & replace in files.
ğŸ”¥ Production Use Case
Change config port 8080 â†’ 9090
sed -i 's/8080/9090/g' config.yaml
--------->sed<-----------
Change Port Number in Production Config
File: /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
Before:
listen 8080;
You need to change to 9090.
Command:
sed -i 's/8080/9090/g' /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
Explanation:

s â†’ substitute
8080 â†’ old value
9090 â†’ new value
g â†’ replace all occurrences
Used during environment migration.

sed -i s/sairam/prabhas/g file1
[root@ip-172-31-1-122 ~]# cat file1
prabhas
if we use "g" means it will replace every where in the file
